  "texts": [
    "The authors replicated the analysis using SHAP and obtained a consistent feature ranking analysis.",
    "The study employed AD biomarkers that are powerful enough to predict CN, late MCI and AD and also ranked the biomarkers in order of their feature importance.",
    "The study also shows that the Amyloid beta (A), tau (T), and neurogenerative biomarkers (N) have different importance in predicting clinical dementia.",
    "The study proves the high importance of the biomarkers (A) and (T) in predicting early cognitive impairment and the glucose uptake in predicting later cognitive impairment.",
    "The authors also demonstrate a framework integrating A/T/N biomarkers using RF to classify dementia and rank biomarker features.The ML models XGBoost and RF are used in [95,99,104] for AD classification and interpreting with SHAP."
  ],
